    <div class="container" xmlns=""><br><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">SECOND DAY --- WEDNESDAY, JANUARY 9, 2019</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The house met at 10:02 a.m. and was called to order by the speaker.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The roll of the house was called and a quorum was announced present (Record&nbsp;4).</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Present &#x2014; Mr. Speaker(C); Allen; Allison; Anchia; Anderson; Ashby; Bailes; Beckley; Bell, C.; Bell, K.; Bernal; Biedermann; Blanco; Bonnen; Bowers; Buckley; Bucy; Burns; Burrows; Button; Cain; Calanni; Canales; Capriglione; Clardy; Cole; Coleman; Collier; Cortez; Craddick; Cyrier; Darby; Davis, S.; Davis, Y.; Dean; Deshotel; Dominguez; Dutton; Farrar; Flynn; Frank; Frullo; Geren; Gervin-Hawkins; Goldman; Gonz&#xE1;lez, J.; Gonz&#xE1;lez, M.; Goodwin; Guerra; Guillen; Gutierrez; Harless; Harris; Hefner; Hernandez; Herrero; Hinojosa; Holland; Howard; Huberty; Hunter; Israel; Johnson, E.; Johnson, J.D.; Johnson, J.E.; Kacal; King, K.; King, P.; King, T.; Klick; Krause; Kuempel; Lambert; Landgraf; Lang; Larson; Leach; Leman; Longoria; Lozano; Martinez; Martinez Fischer; Metcalf; Meyer; Meza; Middleton; Miller; Minjarez; Moody; Morrison; Mu&#xF1;oz; Murphy; Murr; Neave; Nev&#xE1;rez; Noble; Oliverson; Ortega; Pacheco; Paddie; Patterson; Paul; Perez; Phelan; Price; Ramos; Raney; Raymond; Reynolds; Rodriguez; Romero; Rose; Rosenthal; Sanford; Schaefer; Shaheen; Sheffield; Sherman; Shine; Smith; Smithee; Springer; Stephenson; Stickland; Stucky; Swanson; Talarico; Thierry; Thompson, E.; Thompson, S.; Tinderholt; Toth; Turner, C.; Turner, J.; VanDeaver; Vo; Walle; White; Wilson; Wray; Wu; Zedler; Zerwas; Zwiener.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Absent, Excused &#x2014; Bohac; Lucio; Parker.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The invocation was offered by Representative Sherman as follows:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Jehovah God, we stand in awe of your presence, Lord, knowing that you are not only Lord of heaven but you are Lord of earth. We pray, Lord, that we would conduct ourselves in such a way that it would be pleasing to you, Lord. Father God, you are the great God of all. There is none other like you. None of us are worthy of the recognition that you've bestowed on us. But we thank God that you consider us worthwhile that you would give your life for us, that we might strive to be better women and men to do your goodwill to please you, Lord. For Lord knows that there are so many things that we do not know. There are worlds that we have yet to discover, but you know all things, Lord.</div>
      <div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">We pray, dear God, that we would all seek your guidance, from East Texas to West Texas, from North Texas to South Texas and Central Texas, from the Panhandle to the Rio Grande, Lord. We pray, Lord, that we would all come together as one; republicans and democrats, that we would put aside party rhetoric; that we would be one as you and your father are one. Lord, bless us, the men and women here, from our speaker, Dennis Bonnen, to Stan Lambert, to Harold Dutton, to Yvonne Davis, to Mary Gonz&#xE1;lez. Lord, there's so many of us here gathered today, and we strive to do your will. And Lord knows, we all need you more than ever.</div>
      <div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Father God, finally, we want to pray for the 28 million-plus Texans that we represent, that we would represent them in such a way that the issues and concerns that we express and vote on would comport with your will. And that we would be the same in private as in public. It's in the mighty name of Jesus that we pray. It's in your name that we believe. In the name of Jesus, amen.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The chair recognized Representative K. King who led the house in the pledges of allegiance to the United States and Texas flags.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>LEAVES OF ABSENCE GRANTED</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The following member was granted leave of absence for today because of illness:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Bohac on motion of Miller.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The following members were granted leaves of absence for today because of important business:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Lucio on motion of Hernandez.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Parker on motion of Craddick.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>CAPITOL PHYSICIAN</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The chair recognized Representative J.E. Johnson who presented Dr.&nbsp;Manojkumar Dobariya of Coppell as the "Doctor for the Day."</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The house welcomed Dr. Dobariya and thanked him for his participation in the Physician of the Day Program sponsored by the Texas Academy of Family Physicians.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>MESSAGE FROM THE SENATE</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">A message from the senate was received at this time (see the addendum to the daily journal, Messages from the Senate, Message  No. 1).</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>HOUSE AT EASE</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">At 10:14 a.m., the chair announced that the house would stand at ease.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The chair called the house to order at 10:35 a.m.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 4 - ADOPTED<br class="hardReturn">(Wray - House Sponsor)</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The following resolution was laid before the house:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 4</b>, Granting the legislature permission to adjourn for more than three days during the period beginning on Thursday, January 10, 2019, and ending on Tuesday, January 15, 2019.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 4</b> was adopted by (Record 5):  143 Yeas, 0 Nays, 1 Present, not voting.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Yeas &#x2014; Allen; Allison; Anchia; Anderson; Ashby; Bailes; Beckley; Bell, C.; Bell, K.; Bernal; Biedermann; Blanco; Bonnen; Bowers; Buckley; Bucy; Burns; Burrows; Button; Cain; Calanni; Canales; Capriglione; Clardy; Cole; Coleman; Collier; Cortez; Craddick; Cyrier; Darby; Davis, S.; Davis, Y.; Dean; Deshotel; Dominguez; Dutton; Farrar; Flynn; Frank; Frullo; Geren; Gervin-Hawkins; Goldman; Gonz&#xE1;lez, J.; Gonz&#xE1;lez, M.; Goodwin; Guerra; Guillen; Gutierrez; Harless; Harris; Hefner; Hernandez; Herrero; Hinojosa; Holland; Howard; Huberty; Hunter; Israel; Johnson, E.; Johnson, J.D.; Johnson, J.E.; Kacal; King, K.; King, P.; King, T.; Klick; Krause; Kuempel; Lambert; Landgraf; Lang; Larson; Leach; Leman; Longoria; Lozano; Martinez; Martinez Fischer; Metcalf; Meyer; Meza; Middleton; Miller; Minjarez; Moody; Morrison; Mu&#xF1;oz; Murphy; Murr; Neave; Nev&#xE1;rez; Noble; Oliverson; Ortega; Pacheco; Paddie; Patterson; Paul; Perez; Phelan; Price; Ramos; Raney; Raymond; Reynolds; Rodriguez; Romero; Rose; Rosenthal; Sanford; Schaefer; Shaheen; Sheffield; Sherman; Shine; Smith; Smithee; Springer; Stephenson; Stickland; Stucky; Swanson; Talarico; Thierry; Thompson, E.; Thompson, S.; Tinderholt; Toth; Turner, C.; Turner, J.; VanDeaver; Vo; Walle; White; Wilson; Wray; Wu; Zedler; Zerwas; Zwiener.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Present, not voting &#x2014; Mr. Speaker(C).</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Absent, Excused &#x2014; Bohac; Lucio; Parker.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 3 - ADOPTED<br class="hardReturn">(Wray - House Sponsor)</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The following resolution was laid before the house:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 3</b>, Providing for a joint session to canvass the votes for the governor and lieutenant governor and for a joint session for the inaugural ceremony.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>SCR 3</b> was adopted by (Record 6):  142 Yeas, 0 Nays, 1 Present, not voting.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Yeas &#x2014; Allen; Allison; Anchia; Anderson; Ashby; Bailes; Beckley; Bell, C.; Bell, K.; Bernal; Biedermann; Blanco; Bonnen; Bowers; Buckley; Bucy; Burns; Burrows; Button; Cain; Calanni; Canales; Capriglione; Clardy; Cole; Coleman; Collier; Cortez; Craddick; Cyrier; Darby; Davis, S.; Davis, Y.; Dean; Deshotel; Dominguez; Dutton; Farrar; Flynn; Frank; Frullo; Geren; Gervin-Hawkins; Goldman; Gonz&#xE1;lez, J.; Gonz&#xE1;lez, M.; Goodwin; Guerra; Guillen; Gutierrez; Harless; Harris; Hefner; Hernandez; Herrero; Hinojosa; Holland; Howard; Huberty; Hunter; Israel; Johnson, E.; Johnson, J.D.; Johnson, J.E.; Kacal; King, K.; King, P.; King, T.; Krause; Kuempel; Lambert; Landgraf; Lang; Larson; Leach; Leman; Longoria; Lozano; Martinez; Martinez Fischer; Metcalf; Meyer; Meza; Middleton; Miller; Minjarez; Moody; Morrison; Mu&#xF1;oz; Murphy; Murr; Neave; Nev&#xE1;rez; Noble; Oliverson; Ortega; Pacheco; Paddie; Patterson; Paul; Perez; Phelan; Price; Ramos; Raney; Raymond; Reynolds; Rodriguez; Romero; Rose; Rosenthal; Sanford; Schaefer; Shaheen; Sheffield; Sherman; Shine; Smith; Smithee; Springer; Stephenson; Stickland; Stucky; Swanson; Talarico; Thierry; Thompson, E.; Thompson, S.; Tinderholt; Toth; Turner, C.; Turner, J.; VanDeaver; Vo; Walle; White; Wilson; Wray; Wu; Zedler; Zerwas; Zwiener.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Present, not voting &#x2014; Mr. Speaker(C).</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Absent, Excused &#x2014; Bohac; Lucio; Parker.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">Absent &#x2014; Klick.</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:0em;line-height:120%;text-align:center;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>HR 3 - ADOPTED<br class="hardReturn">(by Geren)</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">The following resolution was laid before the house:</div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em"><b>HR 3</b></div><br><div class="textpara" style="text-indent:2em;line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:0em;padding-right:0em">BE IT RESOLVED by the House of Representatives of the State of Texas, That the following is adopted as the housekeeping resolution for the House of Representatives of the <u class="addedText">86th</u> [<del class="strickenText">85th</del>] Legislature:</div>
